What&#8217;s so painful about doing?
<pre>
# controller
@pages, @items = paginate ...

# view
pagination links @pages
</pre>
If by rolling your own you mean the example in Rails&#8217; docs of explicitly creating a paginator object and so on&#8212;no thanks, that&#8217;s more verbose.

	<p>One place where pagination does totally leave you on your own and reveals its incompleteness is trying to paginate associations.</p>
