  <cite><strong>Alex Bunardzic</strong> </cite> said 3 days later:<br />
  <p>&#8220;Now, did the tone of your article scare me off of Rails forever? No, it didnâ€™t, because as it so happens Iâ€™m an adult, not a kindergartner with an ouchie. I donâ€™t expect the Rails community to hold my hand and talk to me in soothing tones.&#8221;</p>


	<p>According to your own admonition, you&#8217;re an amateur coder. Meaning, you&#8217;re not in a position to decide whether to ditch your byzantine, 2 million dollar investment in some mainstream technological infrastructure in order to embrace the new kid on the block (i.e. Rails). I&#8217;m talking about these scenarios, and believe me, people in these positions are very easily scared.</p>


	<p>If you, as an amateur coder, make a blunder while messing with Rails, your head is not going to roll.</p>
